note.para:
Additional annotations (more or less only the
        @todo and @see come to mind
        here), should be placed after all other annotations.

section.para:
In general, comments are a good thing and we strive for creating
        a well-documented source code. However, inline comments can often be a
        sign for a bad code structure or method naming.

This is also referred to as a bad "smell" in the theory of
            Refactoring. We highly recommend reading "Refactoring" by Martin
            Fowler - if you didn't already.
          As an example, consider the following code:
            Bad coding smell: Comments

               // We only allow valid perso
if (is_object($p) && strlen($p->lastN) > 0 && $p->hidden === FALSE && ↩
  $this->environment->moonPhase === MOON_LIB::CRESCENT) {
   $xmM = $thd;
}
